# =============================================================================
# Palmeiras Korea Dashboard — environment variables (ALL OPTIONAL)
# =============================================================================
# The app runs fully WITHOUT any of these set, using realistic, clearly-labeled
# seed/mock data. Provide any of the below to enable live data from a source.
# Never commit real secrets. Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in values.

# --- Football data (matches, squad, standings) ---------------------------------
# API-Football (api-football.com) — free tier available.
# When set, the football adapter will attempt live data and fall back to seed
# data (clearly labeled) on any error or rate limit.
# API_FOOTBALL_KEY=
# API_FOOTBALL_HOST=v3.football.api-sports.io

# --- News -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Comma-separated list of public RSS/Atom feed URLs about Palmeiras.
# When set, the news adapter fetches and normalizes these. Falls back to seed
# news (clearly labeled) when unset or unreachable.
# Example public feeds (verify they permit usage before enabling):
# NEWS_RSS_FEEDS=https://example.com/palmeiras/rss

# Optional NewsAPI.org key (newsapi.org) — alternative news source.
# NEWS_API_KEY=

# --- Caching --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server-side in-memory cache TTL (seconds) for adapter responses. Default 300.
# DATA_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=300
